```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"software": [
"TensorFlow/2.4.1-fosscuda-2020b",
"protobuf/3.14.0-GCCcore-10.2.0",
"tensorboard/2.8.0-fosscuda-2020b-Python-3.8.6",
"PyTorch/1.10.0-fosscuda-2020b-Python-3.8.6",
"tqdm/4.61.2-GCCcore-10.2.0",
"numba/0.55.1-fosscuda-2020b-Python-3.8.6",
"Ninja/1.10.1-GCCcore-10.2.0",
"scikit-learn/0.24.2-fosscuda-2020b"
],
"resources": {
"gpu": "A100",
"cpus": 4,
"memory": "40gb",
"time": "48:00:00"
}
}
```

The script uses SLURM for job scheduling and resource allocation. It requests an A100 GPU, 4 CPUs, 40GB of memory, and a 48-hour time limit. 

It also uses various software packages including TensorFlow, protobuf, tensorboard, PyTorch, tqdm, numba, Ninja, and scikit-learn, all with specific versions. 

The script runs a Python script named `train.py` with specific configuration and device parameters.
